19:16.281 --> 19:18.700
then I'll come and pick 'em up from you,
okay? I promise.

19:18.784 --> 19:21.078
No. You see,
Tommy said that he brought some,

19:21.161 --> 19:22.621
but I bet he didn't.

19:23.956 --> 19:27.292
Anyway, having two sets can't hurt, right?

19:29.753 --> 19:30.963
No, I guess not.

19:33.215 --> 19:34.383
Thank you, Chickie.

19:53.902 --> 19:54.987
Hey, chief.

19:55.070 --> 19:58.448
No chance you have a ship heading
to Vietnam any time soon, right?

19:59.616 --> 20:02.077
That cargo ship, Drake,
getting ready to push off.

20:02.953 --> 20:05.330
No shit. What time?

20:05.831 --> 20:07.207
1700 hours.

20:08.750 --> 20:09.751
Tonight?

20:10.335 --> 20:12.129
-What, in three hours?
-Yeah.

20:12.212 --> 20:15.257
Goes out of Jersey, straight to Panama,
then straight to 'Nam.

20:15.340 --> 20:17.176
Should be there in two months or so.

20:17.759 --> 20:20.345
But I doubt they need an oiler
this late in the game?

20:20.429 --> 20:21.555
Oiler.

20:22.931 --> 20:25.350
Hey, you're in luck.
They're still one short.

20:28.395 --> 20:30.189
And why are they going out of Jersey?

20:30.272 --> 20:32.357
She's loaded with 10,000 tons of ammo.

20:32.441 --> 20:34.735
Blow up half of Manhattan
if something went sideways.

20:34.818 --> 20:36.862
If Jersey goes up, who'd miss it?

20:38.071 --> 20:39.198
You want in?

20:53.962 --> 20:54.963
Chickie!

20:56.423 --> 20:57.925
You can't be serious?

20:58.008 --> 20:59.259
What?

20:59.343 --> 21:01.929
Please don't do this.
This is the dumbest thing I ever heard.

21:02.763 --> 21:04.932
Dumber than carrying around signs,
calling our friends baby killers?

21:05.015 --> 21:07.184
Don't give me that shit.
I wasn't carrying that sign.

21:07.267 --> 21:09.561
Yeah, but you were marching
with someone who was.

21:11.021 --> 21:13.023
Just imagine being a soldier,

21:13.106 --> 21:15.108
just got home
and that's the first thing he sees,

21:15.192 --> 21:16.193
is that sign.

21:18.487 --> 21:19.530
Please, Chick.

21:20.322 --> 21:23.033
-You're gonna get yourself killed there.
-No, I'm not.

21:23.116 --> 21:26.078
Yes, you are! I don't get it.
Why are you doing this?

21:26.745 --> 21:29.831
It's like you said.
Everyone's doing something.

21:30.999 --> 21:32.251
I'm doing nothing.

22:13.709 --> 22:16.753
Three days' leave?
You got some nuts on you, Donohue.

22:16.837 --> 22:18.463
Nobody gets three days.

22:18.547 --> 22:20.799
What about the engine room?
That's gonna run itself?

22:20.883 --> 22:22.843
Sir,
I worked double-time the whole way here,

22:22.926 --> 22:24.344
and I got all my shifts covered, sir.

22:24.428 --> 22:26.180
I don't give two shits.

22:26.263 --> 22:28.807
And don't talk to me like we're
in the marines, you butt-licker.

22:28.891 --> 22:31.310
No one's getting off this ship.
We're in a goddamn war zone.

22:31.393 --> 22:32.519
But I have to.

22:32.603 --> 22:35.105
You have to? What's your deal, Donohue?

22:35.189 --> 22:38.358
I need to find my stepbrother.
Ricky Duggan, First Air Cav.

22:38.442 --> 22:40.611
Stepbrother?
He's not your goddamn real brother?

22:40.694 --> 22:43.405
No way. You ain't getting three days
for a half-ass brother.

22:43.488 --> 22:45.365
I got a rust bucket to run here.

22:45.449 --> 22:49.119
But he is my real brother, sir.
My mom is his mom.

22:49.203 --> 22:52.289
You know, my dad died fighting in Okinawa.

22:52.372 --> 22:54.833
And, you know, my mom remarried
and Ricky was born,

22:54.917 --> 22:57.503
and we was raised together,
just like real brothers.

22:57.586 --> 23:02.090
You know, I just got word
my stepdad, Ricky's dad, just died.

23:02.674 --> 23:04.843
I don't want Ricky to read the news
in a letter

23:05.344 --> 23:07.054
or hear about it on a phone call.

23:08.055 --> 23:10.599
I would like to tell him in person.

23:11.683 --> 23:12.726
How'd he die?

23:13.644 --> 23:14.895
Stroke.

23:14.978 --> 23:15.979
Linger?

23:16.063 --> 23:19.691
Yeah. Like a week or two.
It got real ugly at the end there, soâ€¦

23:19.775 --> 23:21.151
Where's this stepbrother?

23:21.235 --> 23:26.698
He's up north. The LZâ€¦ Jane.

23:26.782 --> 23:27.783
Christ.

23:28.575 --> 23:31.703
Shit's hit the fan up there.
You could be walking into a bloodbath.

23:31.787 --> 23:32.829
You know that, right?

23:33.747 --> 23:36.166
Well, he's my brother.

23:37.501 --> 23:39.378
You get all the info on the stepbrother
and all that,

23:39.461 --> 23:42.172
in case Donohue gets his balls blown off
stepping on a land mine?

23:42.256 --> 23:43.423
Yeah, all right here.

23:44.174 --> 23:46.426
Okay. You got three days.

23:48.262 --> 23:52.015
It's 8:05. If you're not back here
in 72 hours and one second,

23:52.099 --> 23:53.100
you better be dead.

23:53.183 --> 23:55.644
Yes, sir. You have my word, sir!

24:38.520 --> 24:42.357
Hey,
you guys ain't with the 127th MP Company?

24:42.858 --> 24:44.109
Yeah, and what about it?

24:44.193 --> 24:46.862
You don't happen to know a guy
named Tommy Collins from New York?

24:46.945 --> 24:48.530
Yeah, we know Collins.

24:48.614 --> 24:50.407
-No shit?
-Yeah.

24:52.326 --> 24:56.121
Yeah. You wouldn't know
where I could find him, would you?

24:57.039 --> 24:59.082
-Why?
-I just brought him a couple of beers

24:59.166 --> 25:00.375
from New York.

25:01.293 --> 25:02.961
Seriously, pal,
why you looking for Collins?

25:03.670 --> 25:05.047
No, I'm being serious. I--

25:05.130 --> 25:07.049
This whole thing's full of beer
from back home.

25:07.716 --> 25:10.177
Now, listen, smart-mouth.
You looking to take a swim?

25:10.260 --> 25:12.763
No. Guys-- Look, I ain't messin' with you.

25:12.846 --> 25:14.389
I'm serious. This-- Here.

25:17.434 --> 25:20.812
In fact, you know what?
I got a couple for you too.

25:27.819 --> 25:30.322
Hey, Pete. He's good. Let him in.

25:30.405 --> 25:32.533
Hey, buddy. He is in there somewhere.

25:32.616 --> 25:33.659
-Thanks, guys.
-All right.

25:42.668 --> 25:47.130
All right, which one of you donut holes
wants to get your ass kicked first?

25:50.926 --> 25:53.011
-The fuck you say?
-You heard me, cupcake.

25:53.095 --> 25:54.930
What,
you think that uniform makes you tough?

25:59.142 --> 26:02.020
Come on, bring it on.
I'll stuff you right in that helmet.

26:07.943 --> 26:10.279
Chickie, Chickie, Chickie!
What the hell are you doing in here?

26:10.362 --> 26:11.989
You know, I was just in the neighborhood.

26:12.072 --> 26:13.323
No, seriously. What are you--

26:13.407 --> 26:15.367
Guys, this is my buddy from back home,
Chickie Donohue.

26:15.450 --> 26:16.493
Yeah.

26:16.577 --> 26:18.245
Got some pretty screwy friends, Collins.

26:18.328 --> 26:20.330
Without a doubt. Guess what?

26:21.456 --> 26:24.543
This screwy friend
just came 10,000 nautical miles

26:24.626 --> 26:27.254
to deliver your ass
a sudsy thank-you card.

26:30.299 --> 26:32.467
Like my grandfather used to say,

26:32.551 --> 26:34.678
always ring the doorbell with your elbow.

26:34.761 --> 26:36.889
And that, my friends,
is called the Irish hello.

26:36.972 --> 26:38.515
-Here. Take that.
-Hello, Ireland.

26:38.599 --> 26:39.600
Hello.

26:40.642 --> 26:41.810
Take it.

26:42.728 --> 26:45.981
I still can't believe you came
all this way just to bring me a beer.

26:46.064 --> 26:47.065
Not just you.

26:48.108 --> 26:50.944
I came for Duggan, Reynolds, Pappas.
All the guys.

26:51.612 --> 26:53.947
-That's the dumbest thing I ever heard of.
-Really?

26:54.031 --> 26:56.533
Is it dumber than the time you took a pull
off your nephew's baby bottle,

26:56.617 --> 26:58.827
'cause you wanted to know
what titty milk tastes like?

26:58.911 --> 27:00.829
That was your sister's titty milk?

27:00.913 --> 27:03.123
No, it was my brother's wife's.
I'm not an asshole.

27:03.207 --> 27:04.666
Hey, hey. Wait, wait.

27:04.750 --> 27:08.212
So, I got this from your old man,
$33 to pay off your poker debt.

27:08.295 --> 27:09.713
-Thank you.
-Almeida, what the hell--

27:09.796 --> 27:11.048
Uh-uh. Now we're even, buddy.

27:12.049 --> 27:13.383
What the hell's going on here?

27:13.467 --> 27:14.551
Attention!

27:16.595 --> 27:18.555
Where'd those beers come from?

27:19.431 --> 27:20.557
Who the hell are you?

27:22.059 --> 27:23.143
I'm Chickie Donohue.

27:23.810 --> 27:25.521
And what the hell are you doing here?

27:25.604 --> 27:26.772
Just got off a ship, sir.

27:26.855 --> 27:28.524
Am I talking to you, Collins?

27:32.069 --> 27:33.320
What's your business?

27:35.447 --> 27:36.573
Just traveling around.

27:37.533 --> 27:38.700
Be more specific.

27:39.368 --> 27:43.705
Okay. More specific--
I'm traveling around Viet-- In Vietnam,

27:43.789 --> 27:45.457
and I'm bringing beers

27:45.541 --> 27:48.752
to as many of my friends
from my neighborhood as I can.

27:49.628 --> 27:51.713
You're traveling in country? Alone?

27:53.590 --> 27:54.967
Yeah. That's right.

28:02.015 --> 28:03.559
Understood.

28:05.310 --> 28:06.436
As you were.

28:09.898 --> 28:11.191
As you were.

28:13.694 --> 28:16.405
-He seems like an okay guy.
-He's not.

28:16.488 --> 28:18.031
Did he just have a stroke?

28:18.115 --> 28:19.616
Nah. Don't you get it?

28:19.700 --> 28:21.827
He thinks
your man Don Ho here is a "tourist."

28:23.245 --> 28:24.872
What do you mean? I am a tourist.

28:24.955 --> 28:28.083
-Tourist is what we call CIA.
-CIA? Get the hell outta here.

28:28.166 --> 28:30.169
Man, who else but CIA
would be headed up-country,

28:30.252 --> 28:31.670
dressed like they're going on a golf trip?

28:32.254 --> 28:33.463
No, Erickson's right.

28:34.047 --> 28:36.550
The military brass does not like
to mix it up with CIA.

28:36.633 --> 28:38.552
Yeah, that's the quickest way
to get your ass reassigned

28:38.635 --> 28:39.636
to combat patrol.

28:40.971 --> 28:45.350
You're kidding me. He thinks I'm CIA?
Like James Bond?

28:47.728 --> 28:50.439
Well, in that caseâ€¦

28:58.113 --> 28:59.740
Yeah, come on!

29:14.338 --> 29:16.298
-Reynolds is over there.
-Yeah.

29:16.381 --> 29:20.385
Duggan's up here somewhere and Pappas is--

29:20.469 --> 29:22.513
He's right around the ammo dump,
right here.

29:23.013 --> 29:26.683
Soâ€¦ I mean,
what's my plan of attack, I guess?

29:26.767 --> 29:28.018
How much time you got?

29:30.145 --> 29:31.647
Forty-seven hours.

29:32.314 --> 29:33.524
It's gonna be tight.

29:34.483 --> 29:39.863
What if he starts up here with Duggan
and then hustles down toâ€¦

29:39.947 --> 29:41.698
-Reynolds. Yeah.
-â€¦Reynolds.

29:41.782 --> 29:44.743
And then back down to Pappas?

29:45.661 --> 29:48.580
